            "body": "For context, I think the only two interfaces we have with a \"class\" implementation are the client object in the built-in language server client and parts of the treesitter interface (queries for one). I think Path and URI are good candidates for the reasons mentioned in #16800 (mostly the existence of Windows to be honest) but I generally think we should prefer primitives.",
